Having regard to Council Decision 80/156/EEC of 21 January 1980 setting up an Advisory Committee on the Training of Midwives (1), and in particular Articles 3 and 4 thereof,
Having regard to the Act of Accession of 1994, and in particular Article 165(1) thereof,
Whereas, under the terms of Article 3 of the abovementioned Decision, the said Committee is composed of three experts per Member State and an alternate for each of those experts; whereas, under the terms of Article 4 of the same Decision, the term of office of those experts and alternates runs for three years;
Whereas, by its Decision of 7 November 1995 (2), the Council appointed members and alternates of the Advisory Committee on the Training of Midwives for the period from 23 October 1995 to 22 October 1998;
